DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260615
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260616
SUMMARY:Kettlebell Doubles 20-30 Min EMOM
DESCRIPTION:Double KB EMOM (progress toward 10 reps/12kg for 30 min). Stack with Daily Mobility Routine and Push Up EMOM 10 Min.\n# Kettlebell Doubles 20-30 Min EMOM\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `20-30 min`\n- Precedence: `primary`\n- Format: `EMOM`\n- Equipment: `double kettlebells`\n\n## Summary\n\nDouble-kettlebell EMOM built around the core power and strength patterns.\n\n## Work\n\n- Swings\n- Squats\n- Cleans\n- Presses\n- Rows\n\n# Notes\n\n- Start with 12-16 kg and 6-8 reps for 20 minutes.\n- Work up to 10 swings.\n- Increase duration toward 30 minutes\, dropping reps as needed.\n- Once you can hold 10 reps for 30 minutes across the board\, repeat at a heavier weight.\n\n## Source\n\n- https://youtube.com/shorts/YVSWjN7CPFo?lc=UgxfFSvUIMg61ILclJd4AaABAg&si=L4rxxK4HUzv0h9j8\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d603d21f23dd-02@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260618T222056Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260616
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260617
SUMMARY:Push Up EMOM 10 Min
DESCRIPTION:Push Up EMOM. Add The Stack Foundation and Golf Mobility Warmup for swing speed.\n# Push Up EMOM 10 Min\n\n- Domain: `bodyweight`\n- Session Duration: `10 min`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Frequency: `2-4x/week`\n- Format: `EMOM`\n- Equipment: `none`\n\n## Summary\n\nProgressive push-up EMOM built around a sustainable rep target that you can repeat every minute for 10 minutes.\n\n## Work\n\n- Pick a push-up number you can complete every minute on the minute for 10 minutes.\n- Example: 5 push-ups per minute for 10 minutes = 50 total push-ups.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Try to increase the rep target every few weeks.\n- Repeat this workout consistently 2-4 times per week.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d603d21f23dd-03@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260618T222056Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260617
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260618
SUMMARY:Suitcase Carry
DESCRIPTION:1 mile suitcase carry challenge. Pair with Hip Mobility circuit and Project 120 - Bands Weekday 1.\n# Suitcase Carry\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `~20-25 min`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Frequency: `2-3x/week`\n- Format: `carry`\n- Equipment: `single kettlebell`\n\n## Summary\n\nLoaded carry performed one arm at a time in a suitcase hold\, alternating sides periodically.\n\n## Work\n\n- Carry a single kettlebell for one mile.\n- Use a suitcase hold.\n- Switch arms periodically.\n- Try not to put the bell down.\n- If needed\, perform a single-arm deadlift to switch arms.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Use a kettlebell around 20-30% of body weight.\n- Keep posture tall and controlled throughout the carry.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d603d21f23dd-04@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260618T222056Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260618
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260619
SUMMARY:Kettlebell 30 Min
DESCRIPTION:Single kettlebell AMRAP circuit for conditioning and strength. Add Daily Mobility Routine.\n# Kettlebell 30 Min\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `30 min`\n- Precedence: `primary`\n- Format: `AMRAP`\n- Equipment: `kettlebell`\n\n## Summary\n\nSingle-kettlebell conditioning circuit with swings\, squats\, presses\, rows\, and push-ups.\n\n## Work\n\n- 10 swings\n- 5 squats\, weight on one side\n- 5 shoulder presses each side\n- 5 rows each side\n- Push ups (50% max)\n\n## Notes\n\n- Perform as many quality rounds as possible in 30 minutes.\n
END:VEVENT
