DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:Suitcase Carry
DESCRIPTION:1 mile suitcase carry challenge. Complete Project 120 - Bands Weekday 2.\n# Suitcase Carry\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `~20-25 min`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Frequency: `2-3x/week`\n- Format: `carry`\n- Equipment: `single kettlebell`\n\n## Summary\n\nLoaded carry performed one arm at a time in a suitcase hold\, alternating sides periodically.\n\n## Work\n\n- Carry a single kettlebell for one mile.\n- Use a suitcase hold.\n- Switch arms periodically.\n- Try not to put the bell down.\n- If needed\, perform a single-arm deadlift to switch arms.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Use a kettlebell around 20-30% of body weight.\n- Keep posture tall and controlled throughout the carry.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d603d21f23dd-29@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260618T222056Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260713
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260714
SUMMARY:Kettlebell Doubles 20-30 Min EMOM
DESCRIPTION:Double KB EMOM. Pair with Hip Mobility or Daily Mobility Routine. Optional Push Up EMOM 10 Min.\n# Kettlebell Doubles 20-30 Min EMOM\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `20-30 min`\n- Precedence: `primary`\n- Format: `EMOM`\n- Equipment: `double kettlebells`\n\n## Summary\n\nDouble-kettlebell EMOM built around the core power and strength patterns.\n\n## Work\n\n- Swings\n- Squats\n- Cleans\n- Presses\n- Rows\n\n# Notes\n\n- Start with 12-16 kg and 6-8 reps for 20 minutes.\n- Work up to 10 swings.\n- Increase duration toward 30 minutes\, dropping reps as needed.\n- Once you can hold 10 reps for 30 minutes across the board\, repeat at a heavier weight.\n\n## Source\n\n- https://youtube.com/shorts/YVSWjN7CPFo?lc=UgxfFSvUIMg61ILclJd4AaABAg&si=L4rxxK4HUzv0h9j8\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d603d21f23dd-30@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260618T222056Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260714
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260715
SUMMARY:Push Up EMOM 10 Min
DESCRIPTION:Push Up EMOM. Complete The Stack Foundation.\n# Push Up EMOM 10 Min\n\n- Domain: `bodyweight`\n- Session Duration: `10 min`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Frequency: `2-4x/week`\n- Format: `EMOM`\n- Equipment: `none`\n\n## Summary\n\nProgressive push-up EMOM built around a sustainable rep target that you can repeat every minute for 10 minutes.\n\n## Work\n\n- Pick a push-up number you can complete every minute on the minute for 10 minutes.\n- Example: 5 push-ups per minute for 10 minutes = 50 total push-ups.\n\n## Notes\n\n- Try to increase the rep target every few weeks.\n- Repeat this workout consistently 2-4 times per week.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d603d21f23dd-31@coach_zed
DTSTAMP:20260618T222056Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Kettlebell Halos 10 Min
DESCRIPTION:Kettlebell halos for shoulder mobility. Stack with Daily Mobility Routine and Project 120 - Bands Weekday 1.\n# Kettlebell Halos 10 Min\n\n- Domain: `kettlebells`\n- Session Duration: `10 min`\n- Precedence: `complementary`\n- Format: `30 sec on / 30 sec off`\n- Equipment: `kettlebell up to 16 kg`\n\n## Summary\n\nHalo practice focused on smooth control and repeatable reps.\n\n## Work\n\n- Wrestler halos: left - center - right - center - up-and-over - back to start\n\n## Notes\n\n- Count reps and try to beat your best.\n- Keep the movement smooth.\n
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d603d21f23dd-32@coach_zed
